.TH PASSMGR "1" "December 2025" "passmgr 202208211301-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
passmgr \- wrapper for the pass (password-store) command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B passmgr
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,PASS-COMMANDS\/\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B passmgr
is a convenient wrapper around the
.B pass
command, which is the standard Unix password manager. It provides a simplified interface to password-store.org's pass utility while adding enhanced features like colorized output, configuration management, and easy account listing.
.PP
pass is a password manager that stores encrypted passwords in a simple directory structure using GPG encryption. Each password lives in a gpg-encrypted file whose filename is the title of the website or resource that requires the password. These encrypted files may be organized into meaningful folder hierarchies, copied from computer to computer, and manipulated using standard command line file management utilities.
.PP
passmgr acts as a transparent wrapper - any pass command can be used through passmgr, which will pass them through to the underlying pass utility while providing additional functionality like automatic password store backup, colored output, and simplified account listing.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B update
Install or update the pass utility to the latest version
.TP
.B (no arguments)
When run without arguments, list all stored passwords/accounts in the password store
.TP
.B All pass commands
passmgr transparently passes through all standard pass commands. Common commands include:
.RS
.TP
.B init
\fI\,gpg-id\/\fR
Initialize new password store with GPG key
.TP
.B ls
\fI\,[subfolder]\/\fR
List passwords (equivalent to running passmgr with no args)
.TP
.B find
\fI\,pass-names\/\fR...
Search for password filenames matching pattern
.TP
.B show
\fI\,[--clip[=line-number],\/\fR \fI\,-c[line-number]]\/\fR \fI\,pass-name\/\fR
Display or copy password to clipboard
.TP
.B grep
\fI\,search-string\/\fR
Search password file contents
.TP
.B insert
\fI\,[--echo,\/\fR \fI\,-e\/\fR | \fI\,--multiline,\/\fR \fI\,-m]\/\fR \fI\,pass-name\/\fR
Insert new password
.TP
.B edit
\fI\,pass-name\/\fR
Edit password entry with $EDITOR
.TP
.B generate
\fI\,[--no-symbols,\/\fR \fI\,-n]\/\fR \fI\,[--clip,\/\fR \fI\,-c]\/\fR \fI\,[--in-place,\/\fR \fI\,-i]\/\fR \fI\,[--force,\/\fR \fI\,-f]\/\fR \fI\,pass-name\/\fR \fI\,[pass-length]\/\fR
Generate new password
.TP
.B rm
\fI\,[--recursive,\/\fR \fI\,-r]\/\fR \fI\,[--force,\/\fR \fI\,-f]\/\fR \fI\,pass-name\/\fR
Remove password
.TP
.B mv
\fI\,[--force,\/\fR \fI\,-f]\/\fR \fI\,old-path\/\fR \fI\,new-path\/\fR
Rename or move password
.TP
.B cp
\fI\,[--force,\/\fR \fI\,-f]\/\fR \fI\,old-path\/\fR \fI\,new-path\/\fR
Copy password
.TP
.B git
\fI\,git-command-args\/\fR...
Execute git command inside password store
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output (useful for piping or logging)
.TP
.BR \-\-dir " " \fI\,<directory>\/\fR
Set the password store directory (overrides PASSWORD_STORE_DIR)
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic Usage
.TP
.B passmgr
List all stored passwords
.TP
.B passmgr show email/gmail
Display Gmail password
.TP
.B passmgr show \-c email/gmail
Copy Gmail password to clipboard
.TP
.B passmgr insert social/twitter
Add new Twitter password (prompts for password)
.TP
.B passmgr generate social/reddit 20
Generate 20-character password for Reddit
.TP
.B passmgr generate \-c banking/chase 30
Generate 30-character password and copy to clipboard
.TP
.B passmgr edit work/vpn
Edit VPN password entry in $EDITOR
.TP
.B passmgr rm old-account/unused
Remove unused password
.TP
.B passmgr mv email/old-gmail email/new-gmail
Rename password entry
.TP
.B passmgr find gmail
Search for all entries containing "gmail"
.TP
.B passmgr grep username
Search password file contents for "username"
.SS Git Integration
.TP
.B passmgr git init
Initialize git repository in password store
.TP
.B passmgr git remote add origin <url>
Add remote git repository
.TP
.B passmgr git push
Push password changes to remote
.TP
.B passmgr git pull
Pull password updates from remote
.TP
.B passmgr git log
View password store change history
.SS Advanced Usage
.TP
.B passmgr insert \-m work/database
Insert multi-line password (e.g., with username on second line)
.TP
.B passmgr generate \-n website/kid-site 12
Generate 12-character password without symbols
.TP
.B passmgr show \-c2 work/vpn
Copy second line (e.g., username) to clipboard
.TP
.B passmgr update
Update pass utility to latest version
.SH CONFIGURATION
passmgr can be configured through its configuration file or environment variables.
.SS Configuration File
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/passmgr/settings.conf
Main configuration file supporting the following settings:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
PASSWORD_STORE_DIR - Password store directory location
.IP \(bu 2
PASSWORD_STORE_KEY - GPG key ID for encryption
.IP \(bu 2
PASSWORD_STORE_CLIP_TIME - Clipboard clear time (default: 45 seconds)
.IP \(bu 2
PASSWORD_STORE_UMASK - File creation permissions mask
.IP \(bu 2
PASSWORD_STORE_ENABLE_EXTENSIONS - Enable pass extensions
.IP \(bu 2
PASSWORD_STORE_EXTENSIONS_DIR - Extensions directory
.IP \(bu 2
PASSWORD_STORE_BACKUP - Backup location for password store
.IP \(bu 2
PASSMGR_GIT_URL - Git remote URL for password store
.IP \(bu 2
PASSMGR_UPDATE_URL - URL for updating pass utility
.RE
.SS Environment Variables
.TP
.B PASSWORD_STORE_DIR
Override default password store location (default: ~/.password-store)
.TP
.B PASSWORD_STORE_KEY
GPG key ID to use for encryption/decryption
.TP
.B PASSWORD_STORE_CLIP_TIME
Number of seconds before clearing clipboard (default: 45)
.TP
.B PASSWORD_STORE_UMASK
Set umask for password file creation (default: 077)
.TP
.B EDITOR
Text editor for editing passwords (default: vi)
.TP
.B PASSMGR_CONFIG_DIR
Override configuration directory location
.TP
.B PASSMGR_NOTIFY_ENABLED
Enable/disable desktop notifications (default: yes)
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.password-store/
Default password store directory containing encrypted password files
.TP
.B ~/.password-store/.gpg-id
GPG key ID used for password encryption
.TP
.B ~/.password-store/.git/
Git repository for password store versioning
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/passmgr/settings.conf
passmgr configuration file
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/passmgr/backups/
Configuration backup directory
.TP
.B ~/.local/log/passmgr/
Log file directory
.TP
.B ~/.cache/passmgr/
Cache directory for temporary files
.SH PASSWORD ORGANIZATION
Passwords are organized in a hierarchical directory structure:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
~/.password-store/
\[char46]\[char46]/email/
\[char46]\[char46]\[char46]\[char46]/personal-gmail.gpg
\[char46]\[char46]\[char46]\[char46]/work-outlook.gpg
\[char46]\[char46]/banking/
\[char46]\[char46]\[char46]\[char46]/chase.gpg
\[char46]\[char46]\[char46]\[char46]/wells-fargo.gpg
\[char46]\[char46]/social/
\[char46]\[char46]\[char46]\[char46]/twitter.gpg
\[char46]\[char46]\[char46]\[char46]/reddit.gpg
\[char46]\[char46]/work/
    /vpn.gpg
    /ssh-key.gpg
.EE
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error or password not found
.TP
.B 3
Required command not found (pass or gpg not installed)
.SH SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS
.IP \(bu 2
Passwords are encrypted using GPG with your public key
.IP \(bu 2
Only you (with your private key) can decrypt passwords
.IP \(bu 2
Keep your GPG private key secure and backed up
.IP \(bu 2
Use a strong passphrase for your GPG key
.IP \(bu 2
Clipboard is automatically cleared after PASSWORD_STORE_CLIP_TIME seconds
.IP \(bu 2
Use git for versioning and backup of password store
.IP \(bu 2
Consider using hardware keys (YubiKey) for GPG key storage
.IP \(bu 2
Password files are stored with 0600 permissions by default
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B pass
The standard Unix password manager (passwordstore.org)
.TP
.B gpg/gpg2
GNU Privacy Guard for encryption
.TP
.B git
Version control system (optional, for password store versioning)
.TP
.B xclip or xsel or wl-clipboard
Clipboard utilities (optional, for \-\-clip functionality)
.TP
.B tree
Directory tree display (optional, for enhanced listing)
.SH INSTALLATION
To install pass and setup passmgr:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
# Install pass (Ubuntu/Debian)
sudo apt install pass

# Install pass (Fedora/RHEL)
sudo dnf install pass

# Install pass (Arch)
sudo pacman -S pass

# Generate GPG key if needed
gpg --full-generate-key

# Initialize password store
passmgr init <gpg-key-id>

# Or with email
passmgr init user@example.com
.EE
.RE
.SH NOTES
.IP \(bu 2
passmgr is a transparent wrapper - all pass commands work through it
.IP \(bu 2
First-time users must initialize password store with "passmgr init <gpg-id>"
.IP \(bu 2
GPG key must be created before initializing password store
.IP \(bu 2
Password store can be synchronized across devices using git
.IP \(bu 2
Desktop notifications can be disabled by setting PASSMGR_NOTIFY_ENABLED=no
.IP \(bu 2
Supports pass extensions if PASSWORD_STORE_ENABLE_EXTENSIONS is set
.IP \(bu 2
Automatic backups can be configured via PASSWORD_STORE_BACKUP
